  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">5 event names fire from the correct surfaces: `view_toggled`, `tag_filter_applied`, `three_dot_menu_action_invoked`, `preview_dialog_opened`, `bulk_action_invoked`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Event properties match spec: `view_toggled.value`, `tag_filter_applied.tag_count`, `three_dot_menu_action_invoked.action_name`, `bulk_action_invoked.action_name` + `selection_count`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No telemetry `console.log` remains in `src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl/` (verifiable by grep).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No PII in any event payload (no userId, no email, no document title/content, no raw matterId).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Events visible in App Insights Live Metrics within 60s of firing (verified during dev harness exercise).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PCF builds clean.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` skills pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md shows task 046 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="view_toggled fires on toggle">
      <steps>
        <step>Open Documents PCF in dev harness (instrumentation key configured).</step>
        <step>Toggle list → card.</step>
        <step>Within 60s, verify `view_toggled` event with `value: 'card'` appears in App Insights Live Metrics.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Event fires and is observable.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="tag_filter_applied fires with count">
      <steps>
        <step>Select 2 tags in the Tags filter.</step>
        <step>Verify `tag_filter_applied` event with `tag_count: 2`.</step>
        <step>Add a 3rd tag — verify event fires again with `tag_count: 3`.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Event fires on each change; count accurate.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="three_dot_menu_action_invoked fires per action">
      <steps>
        <step>Open 3-dot menu on a row; click "Preview".</step>
        <step>Verify event with `action_name: 'preview'`.</step>
        <step>Repeat for 2-3 other actions to spot-check.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>One event per invocation with correct action_name.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="bulk_action_invoked fires with count + action">
      <steps>
        <step>Select 4 rows; click Download in bulk-action bar.</step>
        <step>Verify event with `action_name: 'download'` + `selection_count: 4`.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Event fires with correct count.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="No PII verification (grep)">
      <steps>
        <step>Grep for `userId`, `email`, `documentTitle` within trackEvent calls.</step>
        <step>Expect zero matches.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>No PII fields referenced in telemetry payloads.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    Depends on task 002 (AppInsightsService wired + manifest key plumbed). Should ship LAST in Phase 4 so all feature surfaces from tasks 040-045 exist to instrument. Visual Host PCF telemetry (`card_rendered`, `card_expanded` events) is a separate concern handled in Phase 5 (FR-VH-* extensions). The instrumentation key itself is supplied at deploy time via manifest property — this task does NOT modify the manifest (task 002 already added it). PII-safe property design — if `matterId` is needed for grouping, hash it client-side (do not log raw guid).
  </notes>

